[HTTP::Tiny](https://metacpan.org/pod/HTTP::Tiny) is an HTTP client written in Perl and a standalone CPAN module. By default, HTTP::Tiny does not verify TLS certificates. To enable verification, the `verify_SSL=>1` flag must be specified when initializing the `HTTP::Tiny` object.

This could allow potential local-network attacker to perform a man-in-the-middle (ssl strip) attack.
This issue affects all packages that incorrectly use the `HTTP::Tiny` package.

Vulnerable code snippet -
```
use HTTP::Tiny;

my $http = HTTP::Tiny->new();
my $response = $http->get('https://example.com');
```
